<br>
If you're fighting in the planes you'll be far better off using the level 61+ pets. However in LDoN I still use my epic pet for the additional damage output. Mage epic pets proc constantly in LDoN if they're equipped with either one of the mage summoned belts. If you have a shammy or chanter toss a dex buff on the epic pet the things are just nasty on the mobs. Our epic pet was upgraded awhile back. They're still lower level than the PoP pets but are second only to Rathe's Son in hitpoints.<br>
<br>
There are better primary slot items for mages than our epic but there's also a healthy handful of skittle sticks all over the place.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=402042"><img src="http://home.columbus.rr.com/misfitin/images/tweelis_sig1.gif" style="border:0;"/></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dakamar>Dakamar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/9/03 1:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5528.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Nope, he still plays on saryrn, did take a break for like 2 weeks but came back and started  agaian. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=281239">Dakamar</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
